[
    {
        "content": "<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kn\">variable</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">b</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">P</span><span class=\"o\">)</span>\n<span class=\"kn\">def</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">s</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Set</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">P</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">{</span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"o\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">b</span><span class=\"o\">}</span>\n<span class=\"bp\">#</span><span class=\"n\">check</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">s</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"c1\">--{P : Type u_6} → P → P → Set P</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>is there a way to define <code>s</code> to be of type <code>Set P</code> instead of the function to <code>Set P</code>?<br>\nor is it not allowed?</p>",
        "id": 478973715,
        "sender_full_name": "max",
        "timestamp": 1729882981
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>unfortunately, no. if you want to talk about the set containing <code>a</code> and <code>b</code>, you could add <code>(s:Set P) (hs: \\all c,c \\in s \\iff (c = a \\or c = b))</code>...</p>",
        "id": 478974221,
        "sender_full_name": "Edward van de Meent",
        "timestamp": 1729883233
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>What? Your <code>s</code> is a definition that takes two values of type P and gives you the set that contains them both. What do you want it to do, if not that?</p>",
        "id": 478976870,
        "sender_full_name": "Ruben Van de Velde",
        "timestamp": 1729884524
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>i'm guessing have <code>s:Set P</code></p>",
        "id": 478978871,
        "sender_full_name": "Edward van de Meent",
        "timestamp": 1729885494
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>You could use <code>{a b : P}</code> to make them implicit, but I suspect that's not what you're after</p>",
        "id": 478982896,
        "sender_full_name": "Ruben Van de Velde",
        "timestamp": 1729887280
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Here's one of the ways you can work with fixed parameters across multiple definitions:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kn\">structure</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">MyTheory</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">P</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">Type</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">_</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kn\">where</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">b</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">P</span><span class=\"o\">)</span>\n\n<span class=\"kn\">variable</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">t</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">MyTheory</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">P</span><span class=\"o\">)</span>\n<span class=\"kn\">def</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">MyTheory</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">s</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Set</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">P</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">{</span><span class=\"n\">t</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"o\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">t</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">b</span><span class=\"o\">}</span>\n\n<span class=\"bp\">#</span><span class=\"n\">check</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">t</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">s</span>\n<span class=\"c\">/-</span>\n<span class=\"cm\">t.s : Set P</span>\n<span class=\"cm\">-/</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 478983159,
        "sender_full_name": "Kyle Miller",
        "timestamp": 1729887413
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>You can also make this structure a <code>class</code> if that's appropriate.</p>",
        "id": 478983214,
        "sender_full_name": "Kyle Miller",
        "timestamp": 1729887445
    },
    {
        "content": "<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kn\">class</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">MyTheory</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">P</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">Type</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">_</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kn\">where</span>\n<span class=\"w\">  </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">b</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">P</span><span class=\"o\">)</span>\n<span class=\"kn\">open</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">MyTheory</span>\n\n<span class=\"kn\">variable</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">MyTheory</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">P</span><span class=\"o\">]</span>\n<span class=\"kn\">def</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">MyTheory</span><span class=\"bp\">.</span><span class=\"n\">s</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Set</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">P</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">{</span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"o\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">b</span><span class=\"o\">}</span>\n\n<span class=\"bp\">#</span><span class=\"n\">check</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">s</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Set</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">P</span><span class=\"o\">)</span>\n<span class=\"c\">/-</span>\n<span class=\"cm\">s : Set P</span>\n<span class=\"cm\">-/</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 478983320,
        "sender_full_name": "Kyle Miller",
        "timestamp": 1729887488
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>You can also do</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kn\">variable</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">{</span><span class=\"n\">P</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">Type</span><span class=\"bp\">*</span><span class=\"o\">}</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">b</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">P</span><span class=\"o\">)</span>\n\n<span class=\"kn\">local</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kn\">notation</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s2\">\"s\"</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">insert</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">(</span><span class=\"n\">singleton</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">b</span><span class=\"o\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Set</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">P</span><span class=\"o\">)</span>\n\n<span class=\"bp\">#</span><span class=\"n\">check</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">s</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
